# Pre-Commit Quality Gate

Apply this rule only when preparing a change for commit/PR readiness.

## Planning Mode

- In planning mode, do not execute validation commands.
- Defer this gate to execution mode after explicit user approval to implement/run checks.
- If referencing status during planning, label it as last-known and not freshly executed.

## Required Checks

- Run: `pnpm run lint`
- Run: `pnpm run tsc`
- Run: `pnpm run test`
- Run: `pnpm run build` when frontend/server behavior changed

## Documentation Gate

When app/config/workflow behavior changes, update:

- `README.md` and/or relevant `docs/*` files
- `CHANGELOG.md` under `## [Unreleased]`
- `docs/conversation-running-log.md` for major session milestones (when this log process is active)

## Database Gate

If `server/db/schema.ts` or `database/schema.sql` changes:

- Generate/commit migration files in `database/migrations/*`
- Keep SQL schema and Drizzle schema in parity

## Deployment/Auth Safety

For auth/deploy changes, verify docs and env mapping updates:

- `docs/deployment/README.md`
- `docs/deployment/auth0-setup.md`
- `docs/configuration.md`
